article.description: Nick Mayo and Asante Gist scored 16 points apiece as Eastern Kentucky beat Division II Virginia Wise 70-51 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Eastern Kentucky beats Div. II Virginia Wise 70-51
article.linkText: Eastern Kentucky beats Div. II Virginia Wise 70-51
article.story: RICHMOND, Ky. -- Nick Mayo and Asante Gist scored 16 points apiece as Eastern Kentucky beat Division II Virginia Wise 70-51 on Wednesday night. Mayo was 7 of 9 from the field while Gist was 4 of 13 and scored all of his points from beyond the arc for the Colonels (7-8). DeAndre Dishman added 15 points and seven rebounds. The team averaged 42 percent shooting from the field and had a 40-35 rebounding edge over Virginia Wise. Mayo sank a jumper to start off the second period and the Colonels followed that with a Gist 3-pointer and a Dishman dunk to extend their 13-point halftime lead to 19, 41-22, with 17:58 to play. Eastern Kentucky led 34-21 at the break and throughout the second period. Taiwo Badmus scored 16 points and grabbed nine rebounds for the Highland Cavaliers.
